                <ns5:provenance xml:lang="en">…; ? Alida van Leyden, née Van Ruytenburch (1671-1724);{Martin/Moes 1912, nos. 20-21.} ? her great-granddaughter, Sophia Dina (1778-1835) Baroness van Rhemen, née Van Leyden;{Martin/Moes 1912, nos. 20-21.} ? her daughter, Baroness Adriana Sophia Schimmelpenninck van der Oye, née Van Rhemen (1806-42), Huis de Poll, Voorst, near Zutphen;{Martin/Moes 1912, nos. 20-21.} her son, W.A.A.J. Baron Schimmelpenninck van der Oye (1834-89), Huis de Poll, Voorst, as Jan van Scorel;{Martin/Moes 1912, nos. 20-21.} his wife, Jacoba Christina Baroness Schimmelpenninck van der Oye-van Pallandt (1843-1931);{Utrecht 1913, p. 94, no. 95; De Jonge 1932, p. 145.} by descent to Jonkheer Rudolf Everard Willem van Weede (1858-1933), The Hague, widower of Nicoline Adrienne Sophie Baroness Schimmelpenninck van der Oye (1865-1921);{Bruyn in Amsterdam 1986, p. 192.} from whom on loan to the Centraal Museum, Utrecht, 1931-33;{Bruyn in Amsterdam 1986, pp. 192-93.}…; ? the dealer J. Goudstikker, Amsterdam;{Bruyn in Amsterdam 1986, p. 192.} …; purchased from a dealer by an unknown collector, USA, c. 1937;{Hoogewerff IV, 1941-42, pp. 205, 230.} …; from ‘Mr van Aalst’, probably the heirs of Cornelis Johannes Karel van Aalst (1866-1939), Hoevelaken, fl. 140,000, to the dealer D. Katz, Dieren, 1940;{Muller/Schretlen 2002, p. 72, note 172; HNA, SNK archive, 2.08.42, inv. no. 154, note dd. 17 May 1951, p. 3.} the dealer D. Katz, Dieren, 1941;{Note by M.J. Friedländer on photo RKD no. 28050.} from whom purchased by Hans Posse (1879-1942) for Adolf Hitler’s Führermuseum, Linz, 1941;{Muller/Schretlen 2002, p. 72, note 172; MCCP website, file card nos. 4365, 4823; the Linz nos. 1902, 1903 are recorded in black on the reverse of the panels; HNA, SNK archive, 2.08.42, inv. no. 154, note dd. 17 May 1951: this document is not clear on the price Posse paid to Katz.} war recuperation, SNK, 9 October 1945;{MCCP website, file card nos. 4365, 4823} restituted to Benjamin and Nathan Katz, Dieren, fl. 35,000, 1947;{Muller/Schretlen 2002, p. 72; HNA, SNK archive, 2.08.42, inv. no. 154, list of restituted goods.} by whom donated to the museum, 1948</ns5:provenance>
